%N A397609 Decimal expansion of the surface area of a canonical (dual-uniform) hexagonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397609 The hexagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the hexagonal antiprism.
%H A397609 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397609/b397609.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A397609 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HexagonalTrapezohedron.html">Hexagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397609 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Hexagonal_antitegum">Hexagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397609 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397609 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hexagonal_trapezohedron">Hexagonal trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397609 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A397609 Equals 6*sqrt(24 + 14*sqrt(3)) = 6*sqrt(24 + 14*A002194).
%F A397609 Equals the largest real root of x^4 - 1728*x^2 - 15552.
%e A397609 41.676775391274144926549336748304368494496394585574...
%t A397609 First[RealDigits[6*Sqrt[24 + 14*Sqrt[3]], 10, 100]]
%t A397609 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397609 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 6}, "SurfaceArea"], 10, 100]]
